RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 63. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRIFFITH PARK showed good early speed and dictated terms in the early running, set decent fractions through the turn while pressed by BUTTONWOOD TREE, extended the lead at the quarter marker, drew to a clear lead into upper stretch, kept to task under steady urging to the sixteenth-marker and drew off in the final stages. THECHIEFHASTRICKS stalked the decent pace from the inside, lost ground along the turn, made a mild late bid in the stretch run, was not able to impact the winner in deep stretch and ran on to secure second. BUTTONWOOD TREE prominent in the early running, pressed the decent pace into the turn, kept attendance to GRIFFITH PARK through the bend, lost ground to that rival at the quarter pole, chased GRIFFITH PARK into upper stretch, gave way in the drive, was outfinished for second in the late stages and held safely for third. FANTASTIC DREAM chased the decent pace from the inside, was coaxed three wide into the stretch and did not threaten.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 1M All Weather Track CR: 76. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STEIN'S GIRL allowed to settle, raced three wide into the first turn then slipped to the two path into the backstretch run, was unhurried to the half-mile marker, roused four wide into the stretch, loomed at the furlong grounds, made a sustained rally while outside of rivals into deep stretch, drew to even terms in the final strides and was up on the wire to prevail in a blanket finish. DANGEROUS ILLUSION raced closest to the loose pacesetter through the backstretch run, kept a two wide path into the second turn, overtook LADY BLACKBIRD in upper stretch and assumed command into the drive, was set down at the furlong marker, came under pressure nearing the sixteenth-pole, met the bids of oncoming rivals in the final strides, was gamely bested at the finish for the win and just held for the place. MOONSHINE CAT unhurried in the early stages, saved all of the ground through the backstretch run, was roused three wide for the stretch drive, came within aim at the furlong pole, closed between runners into deep stretch, vied for the lead in the final strides and just missed for the win and place on the wire, while well clear for show in the end. SNOW HILL took back off of the quick early pace, raced two wide into the backstretch run, was steered four wide into the stretch, gained ground nearing the furlong pole but was unable to threaten in the final stages. LADY BLACKBIRD sent leaving the break, established the early lead and sped to a clear advantage into the backstretch run, set solid fractions to the quarter marker, came back to the field along the second turn, stopped in upper stretch and did not have a late response.

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Blackbird
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,showed speed,long lead,stopped upper,no late response

ENTRY.COMMENT: took back,4wide into stretch,no late rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 82. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since February 1 Allowe d 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOING TO SHABOOMS prominent in the early running, set the pace into the first turn, conceded the lead to CLASS CODE and stalked that rival through moderate fractions to the half-mile marker, lost ground on the second turn, re-rallied in upper stretch, made a steady advance on CLASS CODE in the drive, came within aim inside of the sixteenth-marker, surged in the final strides and won the nod on the wire to prevail. CLASS CODE forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked GOING TO SHABOOMS into the backstretch run, took command from that rival entering the backstretch and set moderate fractions to the half-mile marker, drew to a clear lead along the far turn, maintained a clear lead to mid-stretch, kept to task under steady urging to the sixteenth-marker, was caught by the winner in deep stretch and held safely in the end for second. MISS EVER READY allowed to settle in the early running, saved all of the ground to the second turn, was steered three wide into the stretch, did not impact the top two in the late stages and offered a mild rally in the final furlong. MISS FLAWLESS (FR) broke in good order, refused to run in the first furlong despite her rider's best efforts, was pulled up prior to the first turn and walked off under her own power.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: EDDIE CROSSWIRE stalked the decent early pace from the inside, tipped two wide nearing the quarter marker and was roused into the stretch run, ran in pursuit of TEAGANS ATM to mid-stretch, reeled in that rival nearing the sixteenth-marker and drove clear in deep stretch to prevail. TEAGANS ATM showed speed in the early going, set a pressured pace to the turn while carving solid fractions, shook free along the bend, drew to a clear lead into upper stretch, was set down at the furlong marker, was caught by EDDIE CROSSWIRE nearing the sixteenth-marker, could not hold off the winner in deep stretch and held well in the final stages for second. MIGHTY RULER prominent in the early running, pressed the decent pace into the turn, kept attendance to TEAGANS ATM to the quarter pole, could not keep pace in upper stretch, weakened in the drive and outfinished HOWDOYALIKEMENOW in the final strides to secure third. HOWDOYALIKEMENOW chased the decent early pace while outside of rivals, raced three wide to the quarter marker, was roused four wide into the stretch, made a mild bid at mid-stretch, could not sustain that bid in the late stages and was outfinished for third in the final strides. CHELSIESDANZIGLITE fractious prior to loading, ducked in at the start and was off slowly, was a bit green in the early running while trailing and did not factor in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 1M All Weather Track CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXTRA INNINGS was well placed in the early stages, stalked the decent pace from a two wide path through the backstretch run, loomed at the quarter marker, assumed command in upper stretch, kept to task under steady urging to the sixteenth-marker and held in a drive at the finish to prevail. LIBERTY WOLF settled in the second flight early on, kept a two wide path into the backstretch run, advanced two wide approaching the quarter marker, angled three wide for the drive, loomed at mid-stretch, could not make headway on the winner in the final furlong and was outfinished, while holding for second at the wire. START THEM UP allowed to settle, made a steady advance along the backstretch run while saving ground, was steered to the two path into the second turn, roused four wide into the stretch, gained ground at the furlong pole, closed willingly in the late stages and missed for second at the finish, while clear of the rest for third. RACE.FOOTNOTES: IDAHO ONCE brushed with WELTON leaving the start, was forwardly placed in the early running, stalked the solid pace into the turn, advanced two wide on the turn and confronted the pacesetter at the quarter marker, took command into upper stretch, was set down for the drive at the furlong marker, ran on the left lead to deep stretch, came under pressure inside of the sixteenth-marker, kept to task while fully extended in the final stages and held on for the win on the wire. RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1M All Weather Track CR: 98. Allowance Purse 31000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOUSE OF LORDS settled in the early running, raced two wide into the backstretch run, maintained his position to the half-mile marker, made a mild gain on the second turn, waited a bit for racing room in upper stretch, was roused at the furlong marker, closed fast along the rail into deep stretch, overtook CAISSON inside of the sixteenth-marker and kept to task in the final strides to prevail. CAISSON settled in the early going while not far back, saved ground while advancing along the backstretch run, loomed at the quarter marker, battled for the lead with BANDERA AZTECA into upper stretch, took command into the final furlong, was confronted by HOUSE OF LORDS inside of the sixteenth-marker, could not hold off the quickly closing winner in the final stages, was outfinished and just held for second at the wire. BANDERA AZTECA forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the decent pace through the backstretch run, took command along the second turn, battled for the lead with CAISSON to mid-stretch, could not match strides with the top pair in the late stages and was outkicked, while holding safely for third. SUPERMAZEL sent leaving the break and dictated terms into the first turn, set moderate fractions through the backstretch run, led into the second turn, lugged out nearing the quarter marker and lost position approaching the top of the lane, raced five wide into the drive, ran evenly in the final furlong and lacked the needed late response. CHIEF WILD EAGLE raced outside of rivals into the first turn, was well placed through the backstretch run while tracking the moderate pace, advanced two wide on the second turn, was outrun into upper stretch and did not offer a late rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 83. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (If a Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive a $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDENSUNRISE broke alertly, showed early speed and set the pace into the turn, set solid fractions while well handled to the quarter marker, drifted out a path in upper stretch, drifted back in nearing the furlong pole and impeded SLEW'S JOY, drew to a clear lead into deep stretch, was kept to steady urging inside of the sixteenth-marker and remained clear to the wire. SLEW'S JOY chased the solid early pace from the inside, lost a bit of ground on the turn, re-rallied in upper stretch, came in tight nearing the furlong marker, steadied off of heels and altered course at mid-stretch, could not keep pace with the winner in the final stages and just held for second at the finish. MY BUCKET LIST tracked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, advanced three wide on the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, lacked the needed late response, was outfinished in the late stages and missed for second, while clear at the end for third. CAPTIVATED DRAMA chased the early pace, kept a two wide path to the quarter marker, lost ground at mid-stretch while still within aim and gave way in the final furlong. RAYS REGAL a bit slow into stride early on, lacked speed into the turn and did not factor in the stretch. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH RUN. IN A UNANIMOUS RULING, THE STEWARDS DETERMINED THAT GOLDENSUNRISE DRIFTED IN AT MID-STRETCH AND INCONVENIENCED SLEW'S JOY BUT THE INCIDENT DID NOT COST SLEW'S JOY OPPORTUNITY OF A BETTER PLACING AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.NAME: Captivated Drama
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace,2wide turn,lost ground 1/8,gave way late
